SIMPLE: clapper
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clapper
<hw>Clap"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person
who claps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which strikes or claps, as the tongue of a
bell, or the piece of wood that strikes a mill hopper, etc. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Bell</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Clapper rail</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>an
Americam species of rail (<spn>Rallus scepitans</spn>).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clapper</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Clapper
<hw>Clap"per</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>clapier</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A rabbit burrow.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>clapperboard</ent>⟦br⟧
